</ul>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Li_Dak_Sum_Yip_Yio_Chin_Academic_Building_(LI)"><span id="Li_Dak_Sum_Yip_Yio_Chin_Academic_Building_.28LI.29"></span>Li Dak Sum Yip Yio Chin Academic Building (LI)</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Li Dak Sum Yip Yio Chin Academic Building (LI)"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p><a href="/wiki/Li_Dak-sum" title="Li Dak-sum">Li Dak Sum</a> Yip Yio Chin Academic Building, previously called Academic 2,<sup id="cite&#95;ref-22" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-22"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>22<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> was designed by architecture firm <a href="/wiki/Aedas" title="Aedas">Aedas</a>. With a total area of 20,900&#160;<a href="/wiki/Square_metre" title="Square metre">m<sup>2</sup></a> (225,000&#160;<a href="/wiki/Square_foot" title="Square foot">sq&#160;ft</a>), it is located on the slope behind the sports complex on the campus, and is equipped with a resource centre, design room, computer room, language practice room, and student dining hall, classrooms, lecture halls, audio-visual rooms, multi-purpose activity rooms and sky gardens.</p><ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional">
	<li class="gallerycaption">Li Dak Sum Yip Yio Chin Academic Building, CityU</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:CityU_AC2_Void_1_View_2011.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="AC2 Void 1, 2011"><img alt="AC2 Void 1, 2011" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/CityU_AC2_Void_1_View_2011.jpg/120px-CityU_AC2_Void_1_View_2011.jpg" decoding="async" width="90" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/CityU_AC2_Void_1_View_2011.jpg/250px-CityU_AC2_Void_1_View_2011.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1704" data-file-height="2272" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">AC2 Void 1, 2011</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:HK_%E4%B9%9D%E9%BE%8D%E5%A1%98_Kln_Tong_%E9%81%94%E4%B9%8B%E8%B7%AF_Tat_Chee_Avenue_%E9%A6%99%E6%B8%AF%E5%9F%8E%E5%B8%82%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%B8_HKCityU_%E6%9D%8E%E9%81%94%E4%B8%89%E8%91%89%E8%80%80%E7%8F%8D%E5%AD%B8%E8%A1%93%E6%A8%93_Li_Dak_Sum_Yip_Yio_Chin_Academic_Building_multi-functional_room_September_2019_SSG_01.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Multi-functional room, 2019"><img alt="Multi-functional room, 2019" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/HK_%E4%B9%9D%E9%BE%8D%E5%A1%98_Kln_Tong_%E9%81%94%E4%B9%8B%E8%B7%AF_Tat_Chee_Avenue_%E9%A6%99%E6%B8%AF%E5%9F%8E%E5%B8%82%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%B8_HKCityU_%E6%9D%8E%E9%81%94%E4%B8%89%E8%91%89%E8%80%80%E7%8F%8D%E5%AD%B8%E8%A1%93%E6%A8%93_Li_Dak_Sum_Yip_Yio_Chin_Academic_Building_multi-functional_room_September_2019_SSG_01.jpg/120px-thumbnail.jpg" decoding="async" width="120" height="90" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/HK_%E4%B9%9D%E9%BE%8D%E5%A1%98_Kln_Tong_%E9%81%94%E4%B9%8B%E8%B7%AF_Tat_Chee_Avenue_%E9%A6%99%E6%B8%AF%E5%9F%8E%E5%B8%82%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%B8_HKCityU_%E6%9D%8E%E9%81%94%E4%B8%89%E8%91%89%E8%80%80%E7%8F%8D%E5%AD%B8%E8%A1%93%E6%A8%93_Li_Dak_Sum_Yip_Yio_Chin_Academic_Building_multi-functional_room_September_2019_SSG_01.jpg/250px-thumbnail.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3264" data-file-height="2448" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Multi-functional room, 2019</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:CityU_AC2_Main_Enterance_2011.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Main Entrance, AC2, 2011"><img alt="Main Entrance, AC2, 2011" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/CityU_AC2_Main_Enterance_2011.jpg/120px-CityU_AC2_Main_Enterance_2011.jpg" decoding="async" width="120" height="90" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/CityU_AC2_Main_Enterance_2011.jpg/250px-CityU_AC2_Main_Enterance_2011.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2272" data-file-height="1704" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Main Entrance, AC2, 2011</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:HK_%E4%B9%9D%E9%BE%8D%E5%A1%98_Kln_Tong_%E9%81%94%E4%B9%8B%E8%B7%AF_Tat_Chee_Avenue_%E9%A6%99%E6%B8%AF%E5%9F%8E%E5%B8%82%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%B8_HKCityU_%E6%9D%8E%E9%81%94%E4%B8%89%E8%91%89%E8%80%80%E7%8F%8D%E5%AD%B8%E8%A1%93%E6%A8%93_Li_Dak_Sum_Yip_Yio_Chin_Academic_Building_facade_September_2019_SSG_01.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="AC2, 2019"><img alt="AC2, 2019" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/HK_%E4%B9%9D%E9%BE%8D%E5%A1%98_Kln_Tong_%E9%81%94%E4%B9%8B%E8%B7%AF_Tat_Chee_Avenue_%E9%A6%99%E6%B8%AF%E5%9F%8E%E5%B8%82%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%B8_HKCityU_%E6%9D%8E%E9%81%94%E4%B8%89%E8%91%89%E8%80%80%E7%8F%8D%E5%AD%B8%E8%A1%93%E6%A8%93_Li_Dak_Sum_Yip_Yio_Chin_Academic_Building_facade_September_2019_SSG_01.jpg/120px-thumbnail.jpg" decoding="async" width="90" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/HK_%E4%B9%9D%E9%BE%8D%E5%A1%98_Kln_Tong_%E9%81%94%E4%B9%8B%E8%B7%AF_Tat_Chee_Avenue_%E9%A6%99%E6%B8%AF%E5%9F%8E%E5%B8%82%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%B8_HKCityU_%E6%9D%8E%E9%81%94%E4%B8%89%E8%91%89%E8%80%80%E7%8F%8D%E5%AD%B8%E8%A1%93%E6%A8%93_Li_Dak_Sum_Yip_Yio_Chin_Academic_Building_facade_September_2019_SSG_01.jpg/250px-thumbnail.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2448" data-file-height="3264" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">AC2, 2019</div>
		</li>
</ul>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Lau_Ming_Wai_Academic_Building_(LAU)"><span id="Lau_Ming_Wai_Academic_Building_.28LAU.29"></span>Lau Ming Wai Academic Building (LAU)</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Lau Ming Wai Academic Building (LAU)"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div><p>
Lau Ming Wai Academic Building was called Academic 3.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-23" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-23"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>23<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> The academic building project is divided into two phases. The first phase is a 20-storey high-rise building, and the second phase is a five-storey low-rise building with a total usable area of 20,500&#160;<a href="/wiki/Square_metre" title="Square metre">m<sup>2</sup></a> (221,000&#160;<a href="/wiki/Square_foot" title="Square foot">sq&#160;ft</a>). It is the tallest building in CityU. Facilities include a 600-seat auditorium, classrooms, information technology laboratories, millimetre wave state key laboratories, restaurants, learning shared spaces, and administrative offices.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-24" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-24"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>24<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> The building was designed by the Hong Kong architectural firm <a href="/wiki/Ronald_Lu_%26_Partners" class="mw-redirect" title="Ronald Lu &amp; Partners">Ronald Lu &amp; Partners</a>. The third and sixth floors are connected to the Li Dak Sum Yip Yio Chin Academic Building, while the fifth to seventh floors are connected to the student dormitory and Shaw Creative Media Centre. There are also terrace gardens on the 6th, 7th and 8th floors.</p><ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional">
	<li class="gallerycaption">Lau Ming Wai Academic Building, CityU</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:College_of_Business,_Lau_Ming_Wai_Building,_CityUHK.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/College_of_Business%2C_Lau_Ming_Wai_Building%2C_CityUHK.jpg/120px-College_of_Business%2C_Lau_Ming_Wai_Building%2C_CityUHK.jpg" decoding="async" width="90" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/College_of_Business%2C_Lau_Ming_Wai_Building%2C_CityUHK.jpg/250px-College_of_Business%2C_Lau_Ming_Wai_Building%2C_CityUHK.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1200" data-file-height="1600" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"></div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:College_of_Business,_Lau_Ming_Wai_Building,_CityUHK_2.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/College_of_Business%2C_Lau_Ming_Wai_Building%2C_CityUHK_2.jpg/120px-College_of_Business%2C_Lau_Ming_Wai_Building%2C_CityUHK_2.jpg" decoding="async" width="90" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/College_of_Business%2C_Lau_Ming_Wai_Building%2C_CityUHK_2.jpg/250px-College_of_Business%2C_Lau_Ming_Wai_Building%2C_CityUHK_2.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1200" data-file-height="1600" /></a></span></div>
