<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Rankings_and_reputation">Rankings and reputation</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Rankings and reputation"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1358620234" /><table class="infobox vcard"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" class="infobox-above"><span class="fn"><a href="/wiki/College_and_university_rankings" title="College and university rankings">University rankings</a></span></th></tr><tr><th colspan="2" class="infobox-header" style="background:lavender; color:inherit;"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1358620234" />Global – Overall</th></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label"><i><a href="/wiki/Academic_Ranking_of_World_Universities" title="Academic Ranking of World Universities">ARWU</a></i> World<sup id="cite&#95;ref-34" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-34"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>34<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></th><td class="infobox-data" style="width:35%;text-align:right">99 (2025)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label"><i><a href="/wiki/QS_World_University_Rankings" title="QS World University Rankings">QS</a></i> World<sup id="cite&#95;ref-35" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-35"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>35<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></th><td class="infobox-data" style="width:35%;text-align:right">63 (2026)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label"><i><a href="/wiki/QS_World_University_Rankings" title="QS World University Rankings">QS</a></i> Under 50<sup id="cite&#95;ref-36" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-36"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>36<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></th><td class="infobox-data" style="width:35%;text-align:right">4 (2021)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label"><i><a href="/wiki/Times_Higher_Education_World_University_Rankings" title="Times Higher Education World University Rankings">THE</a></i> World<sup id="cite&#95;ref-37" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-37"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>37<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></th><td class="infobox-data" style="width:35%;text-align:right">73 (2026)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label"><i><a href="/wiki/Times_Higher_Education_World_University_Rankings" title="Times Higher Education World University Rankings">THE</a></i> Reputation<sup id="cite&#95;ref-38" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-38"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>38<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></th><td class="infobox-data" style="width:35%;text-align:right">151-200 (2026)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label"><i><a href="/wiki/Times_Higher_Education_World_University_Rankings" title="Times Higher Education World University Rankings">THE</a></i> Young Universities<sup id="cite&#95;ref-39" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-39"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>39<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></th><td class="infobox-data" style="width:35%;text-align:right">4 (2024)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label"><i><a href="/wiki/U.S._News_%26_World_Report_Best_Colleges_Ranking" title="U.S. News &amp; World Report Best Colleges Ranking">USNWR</a></i> Global<sup id="cite&#95;ref-ReferenceA&#95;40-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ReferenceA-40"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>40<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></th><td class="infobox-data" style="width:35%;text-align:right">54 (2025)</td></tr><tr style="display:none"><th colspan="2">
</th></tr><tr><th colspan="2" class="infobox-header" style="background:lavender; color:inherit;"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1358620234" />Regional – Overall</th></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label"><i><a href="/wiki/QS_World_University_Rankings" title="QS World University Rankings">QS</a></i> Asia<sup id="cite&#95;ref-41" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-41"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>41<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></th><td class="infobox-data" style="width:35%;text-align:right">7 (2026)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label"><i><a href="/wiki/Times_Higher_Education_World_University_Rankings" title="Times Higher Education World University Rankings">THE</a></i> Asia<sup id="cite&#95;ref-42" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-42"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>42<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></th><td class="infobox-data" style="width:35%;text-align:right">16 (2025)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label"><i><a href="/wiki/U.S._News_%26_World_Report_Best_Colleges_Ranking" title="U.S. News &amp; World Report Best Colleges Ranking">USNWR</a></i> Asia<sup id="cite&#95;ref-ReferenceA&#95;40-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ReferenceA-40"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>40<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></th><td class="infobox-data" style="width:35%;text-align:right">9 (2025)</td></tr><tr style="display:none"><th colspan="2">
</th></tr></tbody></table>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Overall_Ranking">Overall Ranking</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Overall Ranking"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>CityUHK was ranked #63 worldwide in the <a href="/wiki/QS_World_University_Rankings" title="QS World University Rankings">QS World University Rankings</a> 2026, #73 worldwide in the <a href="/wiki/Times_Higher_Education_World_University_Rankings" title="Times Higher Education World University Rankings"><i>Times Higher Education</i> World University Rankings</a> 2026, #54 worldwide in the <a href="/wiki/U.S._News_%26_World_Report_Best_Global_Universities_Ranking" title="U.S. News &amp; World Report Best Global Universities Ranking">USNEWS Global Rankings</a> 2025, and #99 worldwide in <a href="/wiki/Academic_Ranking_of_World_Universities" title="Academic Ranking of World Universities">ARWU</a> 2025.
</p><p>CityUHK was #68 worldwide in terms of aggregate performance across THE, QS, and ARWU, as reported by ARTU 2024.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-43" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-43"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>43<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>It was previously ranked 49th and 48th worldwide in QSWUR 2018 and 2021, respectively.
</p><p>CityUHK is ranked as the most international university in the world in 2024 and 2025 by <i><a href="/wiki/Times_Higher_Education_World_University_Rankings" title="Times Higher Education World University Rankings">Times Higher Education</a>.</i><sup id="cite&#95;ref-44" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-44"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>44<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Young_University_Ranking">Young University Ranking</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Young University Ranking"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>CityUHK is #4 worldwide in the QS "Top 50 Under 50" 2021 and #4 worldwide in THE Young Universities Rankings 2024.
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Research_Recognition_and_Achievement">Research Recognition and Achievement</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Research Recognition and Achievement"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In 2025, about 256 CityUHK scholars were included in the <a href="/wiki/Stanford_University" title="Stanford University">Stanford University</a>'s "World's Top 2% Scientists" list.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-45" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-45"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>45<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Among these, two professors were ranked within the global top 1,000, representing two of the five scholars from Hong Kong universities to achieve this ranking.
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Graduate_Employability_Ranking">Graduate Employability Ranking</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Graduate Employability Ranking"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>CityUHK graduates were ranked 89th worldwide in the QS Graduate Employability Rankings 2022.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-46" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-46"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>46<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Student_life">Student life</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Student life"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Student_residence">Student residence</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Student residence"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Student residences are located on Cornwall Street, near Lau Ming Wai academic building. They provide housing and recreational space for undergraduates and postgraduates. Among them, halls 1 to 9 were designed by the British firm <a href="/wiki/RMJM" title="RMJM">RMJM</a>, while halls 10 and 11 were designed by <a href="/wiki/P%26T_Group" title="P&amp;T Group">P&amp;T Group</a>. Most halls are named after donors:<sup id="cite&#95;ref-47" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-47"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>47<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<ul><li>Undergraduates: Jockey Club Humanity Hall (Hall 1), HSBC Prosperity Hall (Hall 2), Alumni Civility Hall (Hall 3), Jockey Club Academy Hall (Hall 4), Chan Sui Kau Hall (Hall 5), Lee Shau Kee Hall (Hall 6), Jockey Club Harmony Hall (Hall 7), Sir Gordon and Lady Ivy Wu Hall (Hall 9), Hall 10, Hall 11</li>
<li>Research postgraduates: Yip Yuen Yuk Hing Hall (Hall 8), Jockey Club House</li></ul>
<p>Construction work for the 5th phase of the Student Hostel project at Whitehead, Ma On Shan commenced in March 2022. The student residence was in use in  August 2024, consisting of 6 halls in 3 towers for 2,200 CityU undergraduates and postgraduates.
</p>
<ul><li>Hall 12, Hall 13, Hall 14, Hall 15, Hall 16 and Hall 17</li></ul>
<p>The university also provides off-campus accommodation and short term accommodation for non-local students.
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Student_clubs">Student clubs</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=19" title="Edit section: Student clubs"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Student clubs in CityU are diverse. There are more than 80 clubs from interest groups, residents’ associations and departmental Societies, along with cultural groups including orchestra, choir and debate teams.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-48" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-48"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>48<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Sport_teams">Sport teams</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20" title="Edit section: Sport teams"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Sport teams are mentored by Student Development Services. In April 2017, they have extended their dominance in sports competitions by winning a record-breaking ninth Grand Slam in the 2016-2017 annual sports competitions.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-49" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-49"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>49<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>There are 18 sports teams in total. The university has over 400 athletes in 16 sports events.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-50" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-50"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>50<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
