<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Publications">Publications</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: Publications"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="City_University_of_Hong_Kong_Press">City University of Hong Kong Press</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=City_University_of_Hong_Kong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: City University of Hong Kong Press"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The City University of Hong Kong Press was founded in 1996 as the publishing arm of the university.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-51" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-51"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>51<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> It mainly publishes three types of publications: academic works, professional books, and books of general interest and social concern. The press focuses on China studies, Hong Kong studies, Asian studies, politics and public policy.
</p>
